Shell (Fig. 5
A-D
) trochoidal to narrow-conic, whorls 3.5-4.0. Teleoconch whorls medium convex, sometimes weakly shouldered. Aperture ovate, slightly angled above; inner lip complete, variably thickened and reflected, sometimes forming a rather wide parietal-columellar shelf that sometimes covers the umbilical region. Outer lip thin, prosocline. Umbilicus very small or absent, umbilical region sometimes excavated. Shell white, periostracum brown, sometimes covered with thick black deposits. Shell measurements and whorl count data are summarized in Table 1.
